            "component": {
              "name": "Text",
              "options": {
                "text": "<p>The two most important parts of this structure for the contract are the keys and the user_data&nbsp;. The runtime translates the keys to the memory locations associated with them with the memory that was created with allocate_memory. The user_data is the random bits of memory that the user has supplied for the call. This is how users can add dynamic external state into the runtime.</p><p>Smart contracts can also examine the required_sigs vector to check which of the PublicKeys in call have a valid signature. By the time the Call gets to the contracts method, the signatures have already been verified.</p><h2><strong>Rules</strong></h2><p>A contract implements the following interface:</p>"
